  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  An adult patient â‰¥ 18 years old.

          -  The patient, or legal guardian, has been informed of the nature of the study, agrees
             to its provisions, and has sign the approved informed consent.

          -  The patient and the treating physician agree to attend the follow-ups as defined in
             the study protocol.

          -  Indication for diagnostic and/or interventional procedure.

          -  Lesions in a native vessels where IVMRI interrogation may provide additional
             information beyond angiography and other diagnostic tools.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Culprit lesions within 48 hours following STEMI.

          -  Tortuous vessels, calcified or thrombotic lesions.

          -  Significant stenosis of an unprotected left main coronary artery.

          -  IVMRI interrogation of an unprotected left main coronary artery.

          -  Patients with pacemaker or cardioverter defibrillator.

          -  The patient is suffering from transplant mediated coronary artery disease.
      </textblock>
